      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): honor signed node ids",
        "body": "## Linked context\n\nCloses #61569.\n\n## Summary\n\nFixes #61569.\n\n- Honors explicit `openclaw node run --node-id ...` values across node pairing, registry, catalog/listing, pending ack/pull, node events, and invoke-result identity checks.\n- Uses a centralized resolver (`resolveNodeIdentityId`) that prefers `client.instanceId` (already sent by the node host for `--node-id`) over raw device/client id, falling back when blank.\n- Binds paired custom node ids to the authenticated device owner with `ownerDeviceId`, including owner-checked adoption for legacy approvals stored under the raw device id.\n- Owner-scopes the post-register paired metadata update to prevent a colliding instanceId from refreshing another owner's `lastConnectedAtMs`.\n\nThe instanceId is trusted from the authenticated device connection — the device has already passed handshake auth before the resolver is called. No new auth payload version or signing layer is introduced.\n\n## AI assistance disclosure\n\nThis was AI-assisted. I reviewed the affected gateway node identity, pairing, and node CLI paths and understand the change.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `openclaw node run --node-id issue-61569-custom-node` now appears in gateway node pairing and `openclaw nodes list` under `issue-61569-custom-node`, not under the raw device id.\n\nReal environment tested: local built OpenClaw CLI from `dist/entry.js`; isolated gateway, node-host, and operator CLI state/config directories; gateway started with loopback `--auth none` on an isolated port; no real credentials or user OpenClaw state.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\npnpm build\n\nnode dist/entry.js gateway run --dev --reset --allow-unconfigured --auth none --bind loopback --port 19277 --ws-log compact\nnode dist/entry.js node run --node-id issue-61569-custom-node --display-name \"Issue 61569 Node\" --host 127.0.0.1 --port 19277\nnode dist/entry.js nodes pending --json --url ws://127.0.0.1:19277 --token local-proof-token\nnode dist/entry.js nodes approve <requestId> --json --url ws://127.0.0.1:19277 --token local-proof-token\nnode dist/entry.js nodes list --json --url ws://127.0.0.1:19277 --token local-proof-token\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"pendingIds\": [\"issue-61569-custom-node\"],\n  \"pairedIds\": [\"issue-61569-custom-node\"],\n  \"pendingCountAfterApproval\": 0,\n  \"customIsPaired\": true,\n  \"rawDeviceIdIsNotPairedNodeId\": true\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: the pending request and paired node list both use `issue-61569-custom-node`; the raw device id remains only as `ownerDeviceId`, which preserves the authenticated owner binding without exposing the device id as the node id.\n\n**Not tested:** none\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe node host already forwarded `--node-id` as `client.instanceId`, but gateway code did not have one canonical resolved node identity. Several paths used `connect.device.id ?? connect.client.id`, so the node registry, pairing/catalog state, and some node server methods kept resolving the authenticated device id instead of the requested node id.\n\nThe fix introduces a centralized resolver (`resolveNodeIdentityId`) that checks resolved `nodeIdentity`, then `client.instanceId`, then `device.id`, then `client.id`. The resolver is called at the connect handshake to determine the registration node id, and downstream handlers use it for identity-sensitive lookups.\n\n## CODEOWNERS / owner review\n\nExpected CODEOWNERS review: `@openclaw/openclaw-secops`, because the diff touches gateway auth files matched by `.github/CODEOWNERS` (`src/gateway/*auth*.ts` and `src/gateway/**/*auth*.ts`).\n\n## Validation\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/node-identity.test.ts src/gateway/node-connect-reconcile.test.ts src/gateway/node-catalog.test.ts src/gateway/node-registry.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/nodes-pending.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/nodes.handlers.invoke-result.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/nodes.invoke-wake.test.ts src/infra/node-pairing.test.ts src/node-host/runner.test.ts\n# All passed\n```\n",
        "branch": "fix-61569-node-id-override",
